This paper focuses on evaluating design interventions for self-control on Facebook, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and user behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper also touches on issues related to cyberpsychology (cs.CY), social media (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computer communication (cs.CC).
